-- Russian central bank says shifts boundaries of its floating rouble corridor by 40 kopecks
-- By Lidia Kelly and Alexander Winning
-- Thu Oct 30, 2014 03:08AM EDT
-- None



MOSCOW, Oct 30 (Reuters) - Russia's central bank said on Thursday it had shifted the boundaries of its floating rouble corridor by 40 kopecks a day earlier, following market interventions to curb the pace of the currency's decline.

